## Field Definition ##
**Data Management & Quality** refers to the infrastructure and operational processes supporting clinical data integrity, collection, handling, verification, protection, and database finalization.

This includes:

- Electronic Data Capture (EDC) systems
- eCOA platforms
- IWRS / IXRS systems
- Source Data Verification (SDV)
- Query management and audit trails
- Database Lock (DBL) or data finalization
- Data Protection processes tied to data handling operations
- Monitoring related to data quality oversight

